### 1. Sign Up a New User
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Jane Doe",
  "email": "jane.doe@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePassword123"
}

### 2. Sign Up Validation (Short Password - should fail)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Jane Doe Fail",
  "email": "jane.fail@example.com",
  "password": "123"
}

### 3. Log In (Should succeed and set a session cookie)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jane.doe@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePassword123"
}

### 4. Log In Validation (Wrong Password - should fail)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jane.doe@example.com",
  "password": "WrongPassword"
}

### 5. Get Current User Profile (Checks session cookie)
# Note: If testing in VS Code REST Client or similar, the session cookie set in step 3
# will be automatically sent in this request.
GET http://localhost:3000/api/auth/me

### 6. Log Out (Should clear session cookie)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/logout

### 7. Get Profile after Log Out (Should return 401 Unauthorized)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/auth/me
